
ls - LINUX SHELL COMMAND USED TO OBTAIN A LIST OF ALL FILENAMES IN THE CURRENT DIRECTORY.



combined options (arguments) most commonly used with ls

ls -a - LISTS ALL THE FILES (INCLUDING HIDDEN FILES WHICH ARE NOT DISPLAYED BY DEFAULT, THEY BEGIN WITH A DOT)

ls -A - removes the 2 dot files (. ..) (ALMOST ALL)

ls -l - LISTS ALL ATTRIBUTES OF ALL FILES IN CURRENT DIRECTORY.

ls -t - TIME OF LAST MODIFICATION

ls -tl

ls -r (reverse)

ls -S (biggest sized file first)

ls -Shl
ls -Sr
(combinations)


various options like -u, -d, -R, etc.
